article.description: Kendric Davis and Feron Hunt scored 16 points apiece as SMU easily beat Hartford 90-58 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Davis, Hunt carry SMU over Hartford 90-58
article.linkText: Davis, Hunt carry SMU over Hartford 90-58
article.story: DALLAS -- Kendric Davis and Feron Hunt scored 16 points apiece as SMU easily beat Hartford 90-58 on Wednesday night. Tyson Jolly added 15 points and 11 rebounds and Isiaha Mike had 12 points and nine rebounds for SMU (6-0), which earned its sixth consecutive victory to start the season. Traci Carter had 16 points for the Hawks (4-4). Hunter Marks added 10 points. SMU faces Abilene Christian at home on Friday. Hartford plays Texas State on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
